Occasional music videos we do for songs will still have the live studio sound.

Artists get to explore and experiment, and you get to be there to see it.

PlaylistItems.title: D Billions Live Show
D Billions LIVE SHOW! A Billion Smiles! | Bishkek 2023! Chicky, Cha-Cha, Boom-Boom, Lya-Lya & More!
PlaylistItems.description:
https://band.link/DBillions

Hello, everyone! We have fantastic news! Our world tour has just begun and today we want to show you our first concert which took place in Bishkek, the capital of Kyrgyz Republic. With the support from nonprofit organization "Ene Balaga Tirek" we were able to gather over 40 thousand people! We saw joy and happy smiles on faces of thousands of kids. They had an opportunity to see their favorite characters live! Dear friends, where would you like to see us next?

Happy watching!
#DBillions #liveshow #concert #forkids

PlaylistItems.title: D Billions' Travels
Exploring the World! Cha-Cha, Lya-Lya & Boom-Boom are Visiting Vietnam | D Billions' Travels
PlaylistItems.description:
Hello friends! We are introducing you to D Billions' Travel adventures! Get ready for an unforgettable adventure at the amazing Amusement Park in the heart of Vietnam! Together with Cha-Cha, Lya-Lya and Boom-Boom, you will walk along the paths of the park, feel the adrenaline from high-speed rides, meet unusual animals - from colorful birds to cute camels and giant rhinos! Also, the mysterious world of the aquarium awaits you, where you will learn amazing facts about the diversity of aquatic life!

PlaylistItems.title: Knock, knock, knock! Who's there? (Safety rules for kids) | D Billions VLOG English
PlaylistItems.description:
Hi, kids! This is D Billions Vlog! Safety rules for kids await you in this educational video. Every minute our kids are exposed to different types of dangers. Kids will be able to deal with those if they know what to do in certain situations. From early ages kids must know that people are different and they should open the door only to close ones. In this episode, we have shown this simple rule! We believe that it's important not to scare kids when discussing such topics and tell about them through entertaining stories! We hope we were able to do so. Enjoy watching!

Do you know that the history of ice cream goes four thousand years back? It is said that in ancient China a dessert was server which resembled modern ice cream! It is also known that ancient Greeks, Persians, Romans and Mongols in India consumed chilled milk products, juices and their mixes! Also, there was an Iranian dish called "Falude" (appeared in the V century B.C.), which was made of starch fibers, frosted with rose water, lime juice and sometimes with milled pistachios. In Europe, ice cream was first introduced by Marco Polo. He brought first recipes from China in the XIII century! In the USA, the first specialized ice cream cafe opened its doors in 1945. 

This is a short history of this cold tasty dessert. Friends, nowadays, anyone can make their own ice cream at home! Do you want to know how? Let's find out together with D Billions!

Hello, kids! For today's episode Lya Lya has prepared two games! In the first game, players will have to make a funny face on the surface of a cardboard using attachable eyes, nose and so on. In the second game our heroes will need to balance a piece of plastic cloth to score balls into holes with certain colors. Friends, we hope you will like this episode of our channel! 

Have fun!

PlaylistItems.description:
Hello everyone! In this episode D Billions Vlog team has teamed up with a funny ginger-ginger hamster Biscuit! Our heroes have made a cardboard maze-house! Biscuit needs to find the exit from this complicated labyrinth and get to a handful of nuts! Let's help him out, kids!

 Are you ready for fun?
